title: For Sale:  Rare Sino Soviet SKS
postcontent:
I have for sale a Rare Sino Soviet SKS Carbine. These were made in the first half of 1956 in China under Russian watch, Russia had sent a team of advisor's to China to show them how to manufacture the SKS Carbine. The S/N is to the left of the Arsenal 26 (Jianshe) mark and has a weird letter before the 4 digit S/N, that's how to tell this is a Sino Soviet. It has the correct Russian rear sight and uses a blade bayonet.

Someone has ground the bayonet lug off and the cleaning rod lug off as well. Was gonna keep it and put a new front sight block on it so I can take it back to it's Military form but I've decided to part with it. This SKS functions flawlessly, it's numbers matching except the magazine and stock, which is common with these. Bore is nice and bright with sharp rifling!

The SKS being sold is the one on the top in the pics, the lighter of the two with the sling and without the bayonet, the bottom one(my numbers matching Romanian)IS NOT FOR SALE!

$350 is a steal!
